	(text "For jungle ICs with 0.7Vpp RGB inputs (like TDA8366):\nR1, R2, R3: 0 Ohm,\nR6, R7, R8: 75 Ohm.\n\nFor jungle ICs with 0.5Vpp RGB inputs (like TA1276AN):\nR1, R2, R3: 32 Ohm,\nR6, R7, R8: 75 Ohm.\nAttenuation / divider resistors R1, R2, R3 can be changed to 24 Ohm, \nand termination resistors R6, R7, R8 to 51 Ohm\nfor “proper” 75 Ohm termination."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 111.506 32.004 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "307923aa-e8a6-4733-8a5a-25d2ce4ab937")
	)
	(text "Blanking voltage divider / pulldown resistors values\nare depends on jungle IC requirements.\nFor 3V inputs use R11=1K/1.2K, R12=2.3K/2.8K, and so on.\nSome ICs require pulldown R12=10~50K.\nR12 can be omitted but R11=120R~180R is recommended to limit current."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 86.614 65.786 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "8e7dc137-e3b9-45c6-9c04-692f8ab2de23")
	)
